Key Match Events: Youssef En Nesyri scored the first goal for Morocco in the 30th minute.
Boufal scored the second goal for Morocco five minutes later.
Youssef En Nesyri scored his second goal in the 55th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: These teams have not met since June 2003, where Morocco won 1-0.
The match will be played at the Laurent Pokou Stadium in San Pédro, Côte d'Ivoire.
Youssef En-Nesyri is the great reference in the Moroccan attack, currently playing for Sevilla FC.
Mohamed Buya Turay is a key player for Sierra Leone, playing in the Danish Super League with Odense.
Post-Match Reflections: Morocco confirmed their 3-1 victory over Sierra Leone.
Hakim Ziyech and Saiss did not play against Sierra Leone due to some discomfort and were training individually.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played behind closed doors and was not broadcast.
Sierra Leone finished third in Group A with five points in their qualifying group and were eliminated from the Africa Cup of Nations.
Morocco is in Group F of the Africa Cup of Nations with Tanzania, Democratic Republic of Congo, and Zambia.
